This program will encrypt/decrypt a file passed in the command line using the following switch statements

//note default is -encrypt

-decrypt        decrypts a file and stores the data in a newly created .txt file
-encrypt        encrypts a file and stores the data in a newly created .crp file

if a file has an extension it must be included but if the file has no extension then no extension is needed.
If the file has a '.' in its name then the file extension is assumed to be all characters after the final '.'

Upon success "Process complete" will be printed to the terminal

Upon failure an "Error" will be printed with the files that failed to open,

check if files are in the SAME DIRECTORY AS THE COMPILED PROGRAM, if not use the FULL FILE PATH
the files generated by this program will be in the same directory as the file that was passed.